<div id="comment_status_64137512" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64137512" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64137512" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64137512" name="comment_link_64137512" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23184254&amp;cid=64137512" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64137512)" >Re:Part of the early 2000s XML solves everything</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64137512" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64137512); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>4</a>, Informative)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~vadim_t">vadim_t</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~vadim_t">( 324782 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64137512">		
		on Saturday January 06, 2024 @07:43PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23184254&amp;cid=64137512">#64137512</a>)
		<small><a href="http://sheelab.homecreatures.com/" title="http://sheelab.homecreatures.com/" class="user_homepage_display">Homepage</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64137512"><p>XMPP isn't even good XML. It's weirdly annoying.</p><p>XMPP absolutely requires an event-based parser, because the entire conversation from start to end is a single XML document that doesn't end until the client disconnects. So you absolutely need a parser that can deal with XML as it comes.</p><p>It's also not terribly high performance friendly. There's no clear framing, so the only way to tell where a message ends is to parse XML until you reach the end. You don't get a friendly protocol that tells you "Hey, next message is 520 bytes long", so that you can conveniently allocate a buffer upfront and read the whole thing in one go.</p><p>Besides that, it appears that XMPP's dialect deviates somewhat from proper XML, eg, by not allowing anything but UTF8 and forbidding comments. Those may be fairly minor, but they'd be problems early on, meaning you can run into trouble with the wrong XML libraries/code.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64137512">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64137512" class="btn link" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23184254&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64137512" onclick="D2.replyTo(64137512); return false;">Reply to This</a> <span class="ind"></span><a class="btn link" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23184254&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;cid=64137248" onclick="return D2.selectParent(64137248)">Parent</a> 	<a href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
